    "The scientific community uses the harmonic analysis method to forecast changes in sealevel.",
    "This way, all tidal constituents are separated, which necessitates a time span of 18.6 years or longer of sea-level data.",
    "In addition, much longer periodicities up to six decades or longer exist in the ocean and elsewhere on Earth, as well as in other climatic variables including temperature and CO2.",
    "More accurate estimates of rapid sea-level rise (trend and acceleration) globally and at regional scale potentially remain illusive.",
    "An inadequate time span for sea-level measurements can lead to substantial errors and undermine the reliability of sea-level predictions."
